President Joe Biden visited the Ford Rouge Electric Vehicle Center in Dearborn, Michigan, where he spoke about the future of the auto industry and the importance of investing in electric vehicles. He emphasized the need for the United States to lead in the production of electric vehicles and batteries, as China is currently ahead in this race. Biden discussed the American Jobs Plan and its focus on transforming infrastructure, boosting manufacturing capacity, and supporting clean energy. He also highlighted the importance of the American worker and the need to protect workers' rights to unionize. Biden expressed his belief that America can create millions of good-paying union jobs while addressing the climate crisis. He concluded his speech by stating that America is back and that there is no quit in America.